description: The Americans' streak of dominance in Olympic men's basketball has only grown more impressive as international basketball has become more competitive than ever. The U.S. defeated host France 98-87.
title: The U.S. men's basketball team topples France to win its fifth straight Olympic gold

description: U.S. women cruised to victory in the 4 by 400 relay in Saint-Denis, France. American men, meanwhile, prevailed in a hard-fought relay at the same distance, beating Botswana.
title: U.S. women, men seize a pair of golds in Olympic 4-by-400m relays

description: Chiles won bronze after a last-minute inquiry found the judges had underscored her by a tenth of a point. On Saturday, an appeals court vacated the inquiry, saying it had come four seconds too late.
title: U.S. gymnast Jordan Chiles may have to return Olympic bronze medal after ruling

description: Now that Vice President Harris is the Democratic presidential nominee, Donald Trump’s polling advantage is erased, his messaging is upended and a campaign focused against President Biden has to adapt.
title: A Trump campaign built to battle Biden is forced to recalibrate to Kamala Harris

description: It's the first Olympic gold medal for the U.S. women's national team since 2012. The win against Brazil is another sign of the U.S. transformation after falling short in a string of major tournaments.
title: U.S. women's soccer team wins 5th gold medal, defeats Brazil 1-0 at Paris Olympics

description: Over the past three decades, Susan Wojcicki had a knack for seeing a startup's potential. Her intuition helped shape the growth of YouTube and Google.
title: Susan Wojcicki, former YouTube CEO and Silicon Valley visionary, dies at 56

description: Michael Brown Sr. said, “I’m not gonna never let the world forget about my son,” he told St. Louis Public Radio on Friday. “We wanted to show what he did in his life before the hashtag.”
title: Photos: Family of Michael Brown Jr. marches on Ferguson 10 years later

description: This will be the final Summer Olympics with the current line-up of the five events that make up the modern pentathlon. Gone will be the horse-riding and in its place: a controversial obstacle course.
title: The modern pentathlon, soon to break from military tradition, has last ride in Paris

description: In an election season rife with surprises, you might add this week’s revelation by Robert F. Kennedy Jr.
title: Opinion: RFK Jr.'s Central Park 'Bear-B-Q' stunt

description: Ten years ago, a white police officer killed Michael Brown, a Black teen in Ferguson, Mo. His death prompted nationwide protests and a White House report on American policing. How much has changed since his death?
title: 10 years after Michael Brown's death, police killings are not going down
